Charles Czeisler, professor of sleep medicine at Harvard Medical School and specialist at Brigham and Women's Hospital, is the one who created the course, which is believed to be the first of this type in the United States.
It was inspired to create the course after holding a conference on the impact of sleep deprivation on the ability to learn.
“At last, a girl came and said to me, ‘Why is this said to me just now, in the last year?’
