The culture that makes students proud that they have learned all night still exists, he adds, adding that modern technology and the increasing pressure imposed on students have transformed sleep deprivation into a growing problem.
Sufficient sleep, of good quality, should be a student's "secret weapon" for combating stress, exhaustion and anxiety, he said, even to avoid weight gain, because sleep deprivation makes the brain think that the body is hungry, which makes the students feel hungry constantly.
Raymond So, a 19-year-old student in California studying chemical and physical biology, helped Professor Cheisler create the course, after participating in one of his courses in his first year at Harvard.
